# 3. 涙雨

Kanade: (Maybe dad will be awake today.)
Kanade: (But even if he is awake, which “dad” is he going to be...?)
Kanade: (Here's to hoping for a real conversation...)
Kanade: Hello...
Nurse: Oh, Kanade. Hello.
Nurse: You came at a good time. Your father's awake.
Kanade: What? He is...?
Nurse: However, it's difficult to say how much he can remember at the moment...
Kanade: Thank you... I'll try talking to him.
Kanade: Good morning. Or afternoon, I guess...
Kanade's Father: Hm? Ah, good afternoon.
Kanade: How are you doing?
Kanade's Father: I, uh...
Kanade's Father: I'm sorry. I'm not sure I got your name.
Kanade's Father: I apologize for not remembering... Apparently, stress from work caused my memory to become pretty jumbled.
Kanade: I see...
Kanade's Father: Again, I'm so sorry. After you came all this way to visit. I can't seem to remember anything about my family either...
Kanade: Your family...?
Kanade's Father: Yes. We're actually about to become parents.
Kanade's Father: My wife's in her second trimester and her belly's been growing so much...
Kanade's Father: I know that I need to be by her side as much as possible, but look at me... How can I in this state...?
Kanade: ...
Kanade: Please don't say that.
Kanade: I know that you're a kind person who cares about his family very much, Mr. Yoisaki.
Kanade's Father: Haha. Thank you. Also, I didn't catch your name...
Kanade: It's Kanade...
Kanade's Father: Kanade? What a coincidence. We're thinking about calling our baby that.
Kanade's Father: My wife and I love music very much, so we're hoping that we'll be able to enjoy it together as a family...
Kanade's Father: Look at me. I'm just rambling on about myself.
Kanade: No, please, don't mind me...
Kanade: I hope you get better soon. Especially for your family's sake...
Kanade's Father: Me too. Thank you very much.
Nurse: He went back in time quite a ways today...
Kanade: Yes, he did... But I'm glad that I got to see him doing so well.
Kanade: Anyways, I've dropped off his change of clothes, so if you'll excuse me...
Nurse: Wait, Kanade...!
Kanade: ...
Kanade: (I have no right to feel this sad...)
Kanade: (I'm the one that did this to dad.)
Kanade: (I don't have time to feel bad. I have to keep composing.)
Kanade: (I have to save Mafuyu. I have to save as many people as I can with my music.)
Mizuki: (Hm...?)
Mizuki: (Is that Kanade...? Oh, maybe she's on her way home after visiting her dad.)
Mizuki: (But I probably shouldn't butt in unannounced. Plus, we'll talk on Nightcord later, so I guess I don't need to go up to her now and...)
Mizuki: Hang on... What? She's not using an umbrella!
Mizuki: (She'll catch a cold if she doesn't... She looks so sad too... Could something have happened to her?)
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: Forget it...! Hey, Kanade!
Kanade: Mizuki...? What are you doing here...?
Mizuki: I'm on my way home from work. More importantly, why are you walking around in the rain without an umbrella? You'll get sick, you know?
Kanade: Oh, I was just thinking about something...
Mizuki: You were?
Mizuki: (Something definitely happened...)
Mizuki: (She's really been pushing herself with that new song too. I can't just leave her like this...)
Mizuki: (But...)
Kanade: I have to finish that song...
Mizuki: Huh?
Kanade: It won't help Mafuyu at all at this rate. I have to keep working on it...
Kanade: Sorry, I need to go home...
Mizuki: Huh? Hey, hold on one sec!!
Mizuki: There's a super cute cafe just around the corner here. Wanna check it out together, Kanade?
Kanade: But I have to...
Mizuki: It'll just be for a little bit! A little break before you get back to that song!
Kanade: Sure, but...
Mizuki: Great! Let's go!
Kanade: Huh? But... M-Mizuki...?!
